'I'm Not Making Music for Money' is the twelfth and final studio album by the American rock band The First Edition. The album was released in 1974 and issued only in New Zealand.
Track listing
Personnel
* Kenny Rogers – vocals, bass
* Mary Arnold – vocals, tambourine
* Jimmy Hassell – guitar, vocals
* Terry Williams – guitar, vocals
* Mickey Jones – drums, percussion
* Gene Lorenzo – Keyboards
